Node.Notes: Could mean "lamp" (figurative for light that guides the life) or "plowing/fallow ground" (figurative for preparation for life or way of life).
Some follow LXX with slight change of word to "snares of death." Tree here assumes something like "they who do this are seekers of death."
Not used as epithet for God elsewhere, but the actions involved in this verse probably narrow the referent to God.
S from previous half ("to do justice") is carried over.
